<html><head><title>HTML Form Snippets</title></head><body>
<h2>Form Elements Template</h2>
<h4>The textbox</h4>

<form action="filename.php" method="post"> 
<!--set the action to filename where you will process the input using PHP-->

Type something: 
<input type="text" name="HTMLlabel" size="20" />
<!-- I am using 'HTMLlabel' for name throughout the template to make a point. 
Obviously these will be different for each form option in your work -->

<h4>The dropdown</h4>
Choose something: 
<select name="HTMLlabel" />
<option value="Thing1">Thing 1</option>
<option value="Thing2">Thing 2</option>
<option value="Thing3">Thing 3</option>
</select>

<h4>The radio</h4>
Click something: 
<input type="radio" name="HTMLlabel" value="Thing1" /> Thing 1
<input type="radio" name="HTMLlabel" value="Thing2" /> Thing 2
<input type="radio" name="HTMLlabel" value="Thing3" /> Thing 3

<h4>The textarea</h4>
Type a big something: <br>
<textarea name="HTMLlabel" rows="3" cols="30"></textarea>

<h4>The Submit</h4>
Click something<br>
<input type="submit" name="submit" value="Submit" />
<input type="reset" name="clear" value="Reset" />

</form>
</body></html>
